## 3 · Product adapter (Required vs Recommended)

Fill this when adopting / after Seed. Pattern doctrine: `lk-bloom/hive/master-build/MASTER-BUILD-PATTERN.md` (v0.5.1).

### Required (pattern)

| Slot | Instance fill |
|---|---|
| Admin program lock | Status above; no unit CP-0 while `seed-draft` |
| Independent audit | Always (never self-audit) |
| Human sandbox preview before PR | Admin: ⟨name⟩ · docs-only waiver process: ⟨link or note⟩ |
| One unit / one worktree / one PR | Worktree prefix: `../wt-⟨product-slug⟩-` · branch: `⟨product-slug⟩/…` |
| Primary checkout on `main` | Path: `⟨primary checkout⟩` |
| Append-only ledger + PREP→READY→HANDOFF | Under this build-master |
| Local safe defaults | See `04-agent-ops/LOCAL-SAFE-DEFAULTS.md` — provider/fixture names below |
| Publisher checklist | `04-agent-ops/PUBLISHER.md` (through merge) |
| Post-merge CLOSEOUT | `04-agent-ops/CLOSEOUT.md` |
| Dual worklogs on CLOSEOUT | Finalize under **workLogsRoot** (above); overview + tech; index README |
| Linked history on CLOSEOUT | Append one unit entry + newest-first row under **historyRoot** (above) |
| CP-0 policy | Mode above; domain + unlock phrase below; full rules in `04-agent-ops/CP0-POLICY.md` |

**workLogsRoot fill:** declare a durable admin path with a README index (e.g. `⟨docs-repo⟩/admin/work-logs/` or `⟨this-instance⟩/work-logs/`).

**historyRoot fill:** declare a navigable archive path with a README index (default `⟨this-instance⟩/05-history/`; products with an occupied number may use another path). It maps to evidence and never replaces WORKSTREAMS or worklogs.

